The paper discusses a new MSc module on End User Computing Risk Management, which focuses on spreadsheet risks and their mitigation. This topic falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) as it deals with the risks associated with end-user computing. Additionally, the paper discusses human factors and best practices, which are relevant to software engineering (cs.SE) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) respectively. The use of spreadsheets also falls under programming languages (cs.PL) as spreadsheets are a form of programming. Finally, the paper mentions the University of Wales Institute in Cardiff, which is located in the UK, suggesting a possible connection to the sub-category of computer systems and networking (cs.CY) in the UK.
